DESCRIPTION:Event Interval: Ongoing event<br>Campus location: Gould Hall
  (GLD)<br>Campus room: Gould Gallery<br>Accessibility Contact: cbeevents
 @uw.edu<br>CBE Categories: Architecture\,Construction Management\,Landsc
 ape Architecture\,Real Estate\,Research\,Urban Design & Planning<br>Even
 t Types: Exhibits<br>Event sponsors: <a href="https://larch.be.uw.edu/" 
 target="_blank">Dept. of Landscape Architecture</a><br /><a href="https:
 //be.uw.edu/" target="_blank">College of Built Environments</a><br><br><
 strong><em>Designing\, Crafting and Building Community</em></strong>&#16
 0\;represents a reflective &#8220\;looking back&#8221\; over thirty year
 s since the design / build model was embedded into the Department of Lan
 dscape Architecture&#8217\;s Bachelor of Landscape Architecture (BLA) pr
 ogram at the University of Washington.&#160\;<br><br>As a unique model o
 f teaching\, learning and community service\, the exhibition includes vo
 ices of past and current participants\, and shows the narrative of its e
 volution.&#160\;<br><br>At the heart of this program\, design / build ad
 dresses issues of social justice\, green building\, ecological and susta
 inable design and supporting students to explore materials\, forms\, and
  responsive design. Employing multimedia\, this immersive exhibition is 
 a mosaic illustrating the diversity of projects\, community partners\, s
 tudent experiences\, and award-winning projects.<br><br><strong>The exhi
 bition will be on view April 1&#8211\;May 1\, 2026\, and is free and ope
 n to the public. Visitors are welcome Monday through Friday from 10:00 a
 .m. to 5:00 p.m.<br><br>The reception for this exhibit will be held Apri
 l 14th from 6-8 pm. Registration opens March 12th.</strong>
CATEGORIES:Outside the School
