DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event<br>Accessibility Contact: g
 alenic@uw.edu<br>Event Types: Special Events<br>Event sponsors: Painting
  + Drawing + Printmaking Program\, Division of Art<br><br>Please join us
  for this unique opportunity to visit the private studios of the Paintin
 g + Drawing MFA students and Division of Art faculty at the School&#39\;
 s Sand Point facilities.<br><br>We will also be celebrating the opening 
 of <a href="https://www.rebeccashippee.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopen
 er">Rebecca Shippee</a>&#8217\;s show &quot\;Bare Assets&quot\; in the S
 and Point Gallery. As part of her full-time teaching position in the Pai
 nting + Drawing + Printmaking program\, Shippee&#39\;s solo exhibition w
 ill feature one 45-foot oil painting. This work was made specifically fo
 r the architecture of the gallery\; the three structural steel pillars i
 n the space will serve as supports for the piece.&#160\;<br><br>Students
 \, alumni and the general public are invited for an evening of conversat
 ion\, interaction\, and art. RSVP is encourged but not required.&#160\;E
 veryone is welcome!<br><br>The Sand Point Studios + Gallery is located o
 n the second floor of Building 5\, Bay C at&#160\;<a href="http://maps.g
 oogle.com/?q=47.684016\,-122.261917(Exhibit+Reception+-+Human%2c+Being)"
  target="_blank" rel="noopener">7527 63rd Ave NE\, Seattle\, WA 98115</a
 >. Please use the entrance on the east side of the building on 63rd Ave.
  An elevator is available for wheelchair access.&#160\;
CATEGORIES:Division of Art
