DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event<br>Campus location: Art Bui
 lding (ART)<br>Campus room: Parnassus Art Rm 007<br>Accessibility Contac
 t: Liz Copland\, enc5@uw.edu<br>Event Types: Academics\,Student Activiti
 es\,Workshops<br>Event sponsors: <a href="https://art.washington.edu/alu
 mni-friends-group" target="_blank">School of Art + Art History + Design 
 Alumni + Friends group</a>\nLiz Copland\, enc5@uw.edu\n\n<a href="https:
 //art.washington.edu/advising" target="_blank">Art Advising</a>\nKatie T
 wiss\, ktwiss@uw.edu<br>Target Audience: Art\, Art History\, and Design 
 students<br><br>A resume isn&#8217\;t just a list. It&#8217\;s a transla
 tion of your work.<br><br>In this hands-on workshop\, you will learn how
  to turn studio projects\, research\, and everyday experiences into lang
 uage that communicates your strengths and interests. We&#8217\;ll focus 
 on clarity\, not perfection\, and help you create a resume that reflects
  where&#160\;you are right now. Come as you are. Leave with a draft.
